# CI/CD Variables Setup

Configure these variables in your GitLab project settings:
**Settings > CI/CD > Variables**

## Required Variables

| Variable | Type | Description |
|----------|------|-------------|
| `DEVLAKE_MCP_ENDPOINT` | Variable | DevLake MCP server URL (e.g., `https://your-devlake-mcp/mcp`) |
| `DEVLAKE_AUTH_TOKEN` | Variable (Masked) | Authentication token for DevLake MCP server |

## AI Provider Variables

| Variable | Type | Description |
|----------|------|-------------|
{% if ai_provider == 'gemini' %}
| `GEMINI_API_KEY` | Variable (Masked) | Gemini API key |
{% elif ai_provider == 'openai' %}
| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | Variable (Masked) | OpenAI API key |
{% elif ai_provider == 'claude' %}
| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Variable (Masked) | Anthropic API key |
{% endif %}

## Optional Variables

| Variable | Type | Default | Description |
|----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `ANALYSIS_DAYS` | Variable | `30` | Number of days to analyze |
| `SCHEDULER_TYPE` | Variable | `all` | Which report categories to run (set per schedule) |
| `AI_MODEL` | Variable | Provider default | Override AI model |
{% if slack_enabled %}
| `SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL` | Variable (Masked) | — | Slack webhook for notifications |
{% endif %}
{% if ca_cert_url %}
| `CUSTOM_CA_CERT_URL` | Variable | `{{ ca_cert_url }}` | Custom CA certificate bundle URL (override the default if cert location changes) |
{% endif %}
| `SKIP_PAGES_DEPLOY` | Variable | `false` | Set to `true` to skip Pages deployment |

## Schedule Configuration

Create GitLab schedules (**CI/CD > Schedules**) with `SCHEDULER_TYPE` to run specific reports:

| Schedule | SCHEDULER_TYPE | Reports |
|----------|---------------|---------|
{% for category in categories %}
| {{ category.name }} | `{{ category.key }}` | {{ category.name }} only |
{% endfor %}
| All Delivery Metrics | `dora_all` | DORA + Engineering Excellence + PR Cycle Time |
| Full Suite | `all` | All report categories |
